**Erdős Problem #788: Sum-Free Subsets in Intervals**

**Question:** Estimate f(n) where f(n) is maximal such that for all B ⊂ (2n,4n), there exists C ⊂ (n,2n) sum-free w.r.t. B with |C| + |B| ≥ f(n).

**Conjecture (Choi):** f(n) ≤ n^{1/2+o(1)}

**Known:** n^{1/2} ≪ f(n) ≪ (n log n)^{2/3}

**STATUS: OPEN**

**choi_upper_bound and choiConjecture:**

Choi proved: f(n) ≪ n^{3/4}

Choi conjectured: f(n) ≤ n^{1/2+o(1)}

This was the first bound on f(n) and remains the motivating conjecture.

**bss_bound:**

f(n) ≪ (n log n)^{2/3}

This is the best known upper bound, proved by Baltz, Schoen, and Srivastav using probabilistic methods and connections to strongly sum-free sets.

**erdos_788 and erdos_788_summary:**

**STATUS: OPEN**

**Timeline:**
- Choi (1971): f(n) ≪ n^{3/4}, conjecture f(n) ≤ n^{1/2+o(1)}
- Adenwalla: f(n) ≫ n^{1/2}
- Hunter: f(n) ≪ n^{2/3+o(1)}
- BSS (2000): f(n) ≪ (n log n)^{2/3}

**Gap:** Between n^{1/2} and (n log n)^{2/3}.
